Breakout

This is a game about breaking bricks until no bricks remain in the gameplay space.
Bricks = a series of blocks (usually 3 in length)
Blocks = a logical and visual entity in a cell

The gameplay space is defined as a grid of X,Y where X>Y.
At the top third of screen are a series of blocks laid out from to cover an entire line.
There should be Z lines where Z = 5.
The grid is surrounded by Walls.

There is also a Ball and a Paddle that the player interacts with.
The Paddle can move from left to right and reflect the Ball when it lands on it.
The Ball starts with downward velocity. It will be reflected when it hits a Wall, Brick or the Paddle in the reflected direction.

Make sure all of the constants are defined in its own file.

Victory = All blocks are removed.

See GameDesignReference.jpeg for what this should look like.